  "notes": [
    "This paper demonstrates that ST3Gal1 enzyme regulates intestinal barrier function through modulation of barrier-protective proteins (MUC2, TFF3, CDX2) and inflammatory mediators (IL-1\u03b2, IL-6, IL-8) in ulcerative colitis.",
    "The study uses an in vitro triple-culture model with Caco-2, HT29-MTX-E12, and THP-1 cells to simulate intestinal epithelial barrier function.",
    "ST3Gal1 knockdown improved barrier function while overexpression impaired it, suggesting ST3Gal1 as a potential therapeutic target for IBD."
